  "description": "A close-up, cross-sectional view of a red onion reveals a spiraling pattern of concentric layers. The layers transition from deep purple on the outer edges to pale pink and almost white towards the center. At the very core is a small, yellowish-green bulb. The texture appears smooth and slightly translucent, with subtle variations in color and density within each layer. The background is a plain, light beige, which accentuates the onion's vibrant colors and intricate structure.",
